# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Database (PostgreSQL) — see docs/database-foundation.md
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DATABASE_URL is used by the app at runtime. With Supabase, prefer the POOLED
# (PgBouncer, port 6543) connection string for serverless/Vercel.
# DIRECT_URL is used by Prisma Migrate for DDL and must be the DIRECT (port
# 5432) connection. Both are read by prisma/schema.prisma.
#
# Leave BOTH empty to develop without a database: the app keeps working and the
# auth dev mode is used. Persisted RBAC/audit only activate once DATABASE_URL is
# set to a valid Postgres connection string.
#
# Supabase example (replace [ref], [password], [region]):
#   Pooled  -> postgresql://postgres.[ref]:[password]@aws-0-[region].pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres?pgbouncer=true
#   Direct  -> postgresql://postgres:[password]@db.[ref].supabase.co:5432/postgres
#
# IMPORTANT: DATABASE_URL must be a postgresql:// connection string, NOT the
# Supabase project API URL (https://[ref].supabase.co).
DATABASE_URL=""
DIRECT_URL=""

# Product name (source of truth for the displayed app name)
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_NAME="JumpFlow"

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Feedback Contínuo (Talentos — EP15) voice/AI increments — see docs/backlog-talentos.md
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Both default OFF. When off, the "Registrar por voz" and "Polir com IA" buttons
# render as "em breve" / disabled and no real transcription/AI runs. The Prisma
# columns audioStorageKey/transcription/transcriptionStatus already exist; the
# provider logic is wired only once the flag is enabled. NEXT_PUBLIC_* so the UI
# can read them on the client. Set to "true" (or "1") to enable.
#   US15.04 — registrar feedback por voz com transcrição automática
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEEDBACK_VOICE=""
#   US15.05 — polir/estruturar o feedback cru com IA (apenas sugere; nunca publica)
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEEDBACK_AI=""

# Auth.js
# Required to sign/encrypt the session. Generate one with: npx auth secret
AUTH_SECRET=""

# Local development without real provider credentials.
# When "true" (and NOT in production) the app authenticates a mocked dev user.
# In production it is ignored UNLESS ALLOW_DEV_AUTH_IN_PRODUCTION is also "true".
AUTH_DEV_MODE="true"

# DANGER / escape hatch. When "true" AND AUTH_DEV_MODE="true", the mocked all-roles
# dev user is accepted even in production. Use ONLY for a provider-less preview
# deployment. NEVER set on a deployment with real data, real users or a connected
# production database. Leave empty everywhere else.
ALLOW_DEV_AUTH_IN_PRODUCTION=""

# Microsoft Entra ID provider (Auth.js). Leave empty to use AUTH_DEV_MODE locally.
AUTH_MICROSOFT_ENTRA_ID_ID=""
AUTH_MICROSOFT_ENTRA_ID_SECRET=""
AUTH_MICROSOFT_ENTRA_ID_TENANT_ID=""

# Local email/password sign-in (Credentials provider, Round 5). Set to "true" to
# enable the email/password login on /login. Requires a configured DATABASE_URL
# (the provider reads User/passwordHash) and at least one user with a password
# (via the bootstrap admin or an accepted invitation). Coexists with Entra:
# when both are configured, /login shows both options. Precedence on the login
# screen: dev > credentials > entra > unconfigured. Leave empty to disable.
# AUTH_CREDENTIALS_ENABLED="true"

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Local auth bootstrap & invitations (Round 5) — see docs/auth-foundation.md §11
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# First ADMIN bootstrap, read by the idempotent DB seed (seedBootstrapAdmin).
# BOOTSTRAP_ADMIN_EMAIL is REQUIRED for the bootstrap to run; leave empty to
# skip it. BOOTSTRAP_ADMIN_NAME is optional (defaults from the email).
# BOOTSTRAP_ADMIN_PASSWORD is OPTIONAL:
#   - set    -> the admin is created with this password (forced change on first
#               login). The seed NEVER logs the password. Prefer NOT keeping a
#               plaintext password in long-lived env; rotate after first login.
#   - empty  -> a PENDING invitation is created instead; retrieve/regenerate the
#               access link from the admin UI. The token is never printed.
# BOOTSTRAP_ADMIN_EMAIL=""
# BOOTSTRAP_ADMIN_NAME=""
# BOOTSTRAP_ADMIN_PASSWORD=""

# Invitation token lifetime in hours (single-use + TTL). Default 72 when unset.
# INVITE_TOKEN_TTL_HOURS="72"

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Supabase Storage (expense receipts) — see docs/despesas-persistencia.md
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Required to enable receipt upload/download for expenses. Leave BOTH empty to
# run without storage: expenses keep working, the attachment field shows an
# honest "attachments unavailable" notice and attach actions return NO_STORAGE.
#
# SUPABASE_URL is the project API URL (https://[ref].supabase.co).
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY is the service_role secret (server-only; NEVER
# prefix with NEXT_PUBLIC, never expose to the client). The private bucket
# "expense-receipts" must exist in the project (Storage -> New bucket,
# public = OFF). Files are accessed only through short-lived signed URLs
# generated on the server after RBAC checks.
SUPABASE_URL=""
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=""

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Automation jobs — see docs/aprovacao-automatica.md
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Shared secret for the cron-triggered job endpoints (/api/jobs/*). The
# scheduler must send "Authorization: Bearer <CRON_SECRET>". If empty, the
# endpoints are allowed ONLY outside production (local convenience) and denied
# in production. Generate one with: openssl rand -hex 32
CRON_SECRET=""

# Email transport for automation reports.
#   "console" (default) just logs the message (and CSV) — safe fallback.
#   "resend"  sends real email via https://api.resend.com/emails (native fetch).
# When set to "resend", RESEND_API_KEY and RESEND_FROM_EMAIL are required;
# if the provider is misconfigured the transport falls back to "console".
EMAIL_PROVIDER="console"

# Resend credentials (server-only; NEVER prefix with NEXT_PUBLIC).
RESEND_API_KEY=""        # obrigatório quando EMAIL_PROVIDER="resend"
RESEND_FROM_EMAIL=""     # remetente verificado no Resend (ex: "JumpFlow <no-reply@seudominio.com>")

# Fallback recipient(s) for the "missing timesheet" report when
# AutomationConfig.reportRecipientEmail is not set in the database.
# Accepts MULTIPLE emails separated by comma (ex: "a@x.com,b@y.com").
# The DB value (AutomationConfig.reportRecipientEmail, also a comma-separated
# list) overrides this env when present.
AUTOMATION_REPORT_EMAIL=""

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Transcrição por voz da descrição (Horas — Melhoria #3)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Seam agnóstico: por padrão DESLIGADO. Para ATIVAR a transcrição por voz na
# descrição do lançamento de Horas você precisa das DUAS pontas:
#
#   1) CLIENTE — mostra o botão de microfone no formulário (NEXT_PUBLIC_* para o
#      navegador ler). Sem isto o mic NÃO aparece e o fluxo de digitar segue normal.
NEXT_PUBLIC_TRANSCRIPTION=""        # "true" para mostrar o microfone
#
#   2) SERVIDOR — seleciona o provedor real e a credencial (server-only; NUNCA
#      prefixe com NEXT_PUBLIC). Sem provedor/credencial a action degrada honesto
#      (retorna NO_RESULT) e a descrição continua sendo digitada manualmente.
TRANSCRIPTION_PROVIDER=""           # "gemini" (real) — "openai" ainda é stub
GOOGLE_API_KEY=""                   # chave do Google AI Studio (aceita GEMINI_API_KEY como alias)
# GEMINI_API_KEY=""                 # alias aceito de GOOGLE_API_KEY
# Modelo do Gemini que aceita áudio inline. Default: "gemini-2.0-flash".
GEMINI_TRANSCRIPTION_MODEL=""
#
# Limite: o caminho inline_data do Gemini é para áudios pequenos (~poucos MB; a
# request inteira fica abaixo de ~20 MB). Acima disso a rota seria a File API do
# Gemini — TODO no provider, hoje áudio grande degrada honesto (retorna null).

# Gate de Termos de Uso (EP-M08). OFF por padrão: o texto é rascunho e depende
# de revisão Jurídico/People (há campos a preencher). Ligar só após a revisão.
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURE_TERMS=""
# Feed social interno (EP-M04/M05). OFF por padrão; ligar para exibir o Feed
# (e, para o Consultor, usá-lo como Home).
NEXT_PUBLIC_FEATURE_FEED=""
